# httpstatus

[![PyPI - Python Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/httpstatus.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/httpstatus/)
![PyPI - Downloads](https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/httpstatus?color=red)
![PyPI - License](https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/httpstatus?color=#44bd1b)

Remembering HTTP status codes is difficult and leads to all sorts of confusion,
that's where `httpstatus` can help.  

## Installation

We recommend using `pip` for installing `httpstatus`.

```
pip install httpstatus
```

## Usage

```python
import httpstatus
import urllib3

http = urllib3.PoolManager()

r = http.request('GET', 'https://httpbin.org/status/200')

if r.status == httpstatus.OK:
    print('Nice!')
```

